com.tibco.tea.agent.annotations

Annotation Type Customize


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value={METHOD,CONSTRUCTOR,FIELD,LOCAL_VARIABLE,PACKAGE,PARAMETER,TYPE})
public @interface Customize

    Customize annotated element with UI attributes.

    Can be applied together with:

    • TeaOperation - to customize UI for invoking the operation
    • TeaObjectType - to customize UI for displaying objects of this type
    Note: when customizations is applied to class that has multiple TEA Object Types defined, the 'objectType' attribute is mandatory and should have the name of the target Object Type. Otherwise the 'objectType' attribute is ignored.

    The value is a string representation of the map (it is parsed using Properties class). The map could contain following attributes:

    • label - human readable name of the element
    • icon - a icon from resources contributed by agent
    • page - custom html page for the object (contributed by agent)
    Refer to the developer guide for the complete list of attributes. The attribute will be available in the UI under .ui element.
